[thinking] **Evaluating encoding and decompression**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering the Accept-Encoding header when it includes "gzip,deflate." In this case, the configuration contentDecoders(GZIP) should only gzip. If decompression of the response fails, there may not be a helper available. I'm curious if a server sending a gzip response can automatically decompress with REST assured, allowing response.asString to return the body correctly. It’s good to explore that. I wonder about the closure running before the request and if there's an issue with coverage due to a failed test regarding a checkstyle class name with underscores.
